documentation.value: (0xc000h)/2^16*80MHz = 60MHz, 60MHz is the maximum RFBIST IF freqeuncy according to data sheet.

\brief This function configures RF LOX2 Gain via Bias \details This function configures RF LOX2 Gain via Bias \param [in] lox2BiasCode - LOX2 Bias code \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function configures RF SSB gain \details This function configures RF SSB gain (SSB Buffer gain codes + DAC Bias code) \param [in] ssbBuff1GainCode - gain code of SSB Buffer 1 \param [in] ssbBuff2GainCode - gain code of SSB Buffer 2 and Buffer 3 \param [in] dacBiasCode - PR DAC bias code \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function configures bist signal tones \details This function configures bist signal tones Frequency defined by f = code / 2^16 * 80MHz Amplitude defined by a = code / 2^14 (relative to full-scale; 0.6V) Phase defined by ph = code / 2^8 * 360deg \param [in] frequencyCode1 - tone 1 frequency code \param [in] frequencyCode2 - tone 2 frequency code \param [in] amplitudeCode1 - tone 1 amplitude code \param [in] amplitudeCode2 - tone 2 amplitude code \param [in] phaseCode1 - tone 1 init phase code \param [in] phaseCode2 - tone 2 init phase code \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function configure IF signal mode \details his function configure IF signal mode \param [in] mode - IF signal mode (CW, Square or DC) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

code.value: rfeHwSpi_modifyBit( RFE_HW_SPI_RX_BIST_MODULE, RFE_HW_RXBIST_IF_TRIG_REG, RFE_HW_RXBIST_IF_TRIG_TRIG_SOURCE_BIT, enable, RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_ARGUMENT );

documentation.value: \brief This function enables/disables signal trigger by TE \details This function enables/disables signal trigger by TE \param [in] enable - trigger control by TE enable or disabled \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function triggers start of signal generation via SW. Overrides Trigger Source back to SW \details This function triggers start of signal generation via SW. Overrides Trigger Source back to SW \pre RxBIST is in on state and properly configured \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function triggers stop of signal generation \details This function triggers stop of signal generation \pre RxBIST is in on state and properly configured \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL

\brief This function changes default register values to new values. \details This function changes default register values to new values. It should be used during RFE initialization. \pre NIL \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures IP from Power Off to Power Standby. \details This function configures IP from Power Off to Power Standby. It should be used by Power Manager for RFE Power Off to Power Standby. \pre RxBIST is in off state. GLDO1 is enabled + GBIAS for LLDO \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures IP from Power Standby to BB Power On. \details This function configures IP from Power Standby BB Power On. It should be used by Power Manager for RFE Power Standby BB Power On for BIST. \pre RxBIST must be in standby state before this sequence. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures IP from Power Standby to BB Power On. \details This function configures IP from Power Standby to Power On. It should be used by Power Manager for RFE Power Standby to Power On for BIST \pre RxBIST must be in standby state before this sequence. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures IP from Power ON BB or Rf to Power Standby. \details This function configures IP from Power ON BB or Rf to Power Standby. It should be used by Power Manager for RFE Power ON to Power Standby for BIST \pre NIL \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures IP from Power Standby to Power Off. \details This function configures IP from Power Standby to Power Off. It should be used by Power Manager for RFE Power Standby to Power Off. \pre RxBIST is in off state. GLDO1 is enabled + GBIAS for LLDO \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function generates default 1MHz sine with full scale amplitude from RxBIST digital \details This function generates default 1MHz sine with full scale amplitude from RxBIST digital It should be used for BIST \pre RxBIST must be in on mode (RF or BB) // TO DO: Check wether this statement should not be: RxBIST must be in on mode BB Make sure RF mode is disabled \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function stops generation that was started with rfeHwRxbist_onetoneWaveformGeneration. \details This function stops generation that was started with rfeHwRxbist_onetoneWaveformGeneration. It should be used for BIST \pre rfeHwRxbist_onetoneWaveformGeneration() \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures selected Power Peak Detector (PPD) in RXBIST HW IP. \details This function configures selected Power Peak Detector (PPD) in RXBIST HW IP, inlcuding enabling the PPD, enabling VGA and setting VGA gain if VGA is presented in the selected PPD. It will be used by calibration and BIST SW unit. \pre NIL \param [in] enable - enabling/disabling PPD \param [in] selectedPpd - Selection of PPD \param [in] vgaGain - Selection of PPD VGA gain \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success rfeError_error_none_e is returned \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL
